{"word":"ἐργάτις","slug":"ἐργάτις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐργάτις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:ἐργάτης'><el>ἐργάτης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a workwoman</i>: as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>laborious, industrious, active</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>working at</i> or <i>producing</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>νέκταρος ἐργ.</el>, of bees, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}